<html><head><style>body{font-family:'Segoe UI', Calibri, sans-serif; line-height:1.6;} h1{color:#2E4053; border-bottom:2px solid #2E4053;} h2{color:#2874A6;} code{background:#F4F6F6; padding:2px; font-family:Consolas, monospace;}</style></head><body><h1>HTML Template: login.html</h1>
<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p>Defines the structural layout and content for a specific web page view.</p>
<h2>2. Code Logic &amp; Functionality</h2>
<p>Uses the Jinja2 templating engine. The file allows for dynamic data insertion using <code>{{ variable }}</code> syntax and control structures like <code>{% if %}</code> loops within standard HTML markup.</p>
<h2>3. Key Concepts &amp; Definitions</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Jinja2</strong>: A modern and designer-friendly templating language for Python.</li>
<li><strong>Template Inheritance</strong>: The ability to extend a base layout (<code>base.html</code>) to avoid code duplication.</li>
<li><strong>DOM</strong>: Document Object Model, the data representation of the objects that comprise the structure and content of a document on the web.</li>
</ul>
<h2>4. Location Details</h2>
<p><strong>Path</strong>: <code>templates\admin\login.html</code>
<strong>Type</strong>: .HTML File</p>
<h2>5. Source Code Preview (Snippet)</h2>
<p>Running typical software analysis on this file:</p>
<p>```html
{% extends "base.html" %}</p>
<p>{% block title %}Admin Login{% endblock %}</p>
<p>{% block content %}</p>
<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center min-vh-75 align-items-center">
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <div class="glass-card p-5">
                <div class="text-center mb-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-user-shield fa-3x icon-gold mb-3"></i>
                    <h2 class="fw-bold" style="color: white;">Admin Access</h2>
                    <p class="text-light opacity-75">Restricted Area</p>
                </div>

                {% if error %}
                <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
                    {{ error }}
                </div>
                {% endif %}

                <form method="POST" action="{{ url_for('admin_login') }}">
                    <input type="hidden" name="csrf_token" value="{{ csrf_token() }}">
                    <div class="mb-3">
                        <label for="email" class="form-label text-light">Email Address</label>
                        <input type="email" class="form-control rounded-pill" id="email" name="email" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <label for="password" class="form-label text-light">Password</label>
                        <input type="password" class="form-control rounded-pill" id="password" name="password" required>
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary-custom w-100 rounded-pill">Login</button>
                </form>

                <div class="text-center mt-4">
                    <a href="{{ url_for('index') }}" class="text-decoration-none text-light opacity-50">Return to
                        Portal</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<p>{% endblock %}
```</p></body></html>